1. Anticipated start date: 23/10/2019;

2. Anticipated completion date: 24/02/2020;

3.Participants/population: Male or female, aged 18 years or older, diagnosed as having had a stroke, with defined aphasia. Studies in English and Chinese will be included. are eligible for inclusion.

4. Intervention(s), exposure(s): Treatment of Schuell language training combined with head acupuncture alone, including ordinary acupuncture, electro-acupuncture, needle, fire needle and plum blossom needle.

5. Comparator(s)/control: Including language rehabilitation alone, head acupuncture alone, western medicine alone, or sham acupuncture, blank control, placebo control and other interventions. Interventions in the experimental group were not included.

6. Types of study to be included: We will include randomised controlled trials (RCTs), published and unpublished, in English and Chinese.

question.value:
10. Main outcome(s): Main outcomes include the Boston diagnostic aphasia (BDAE), Aphasia quotient (AQ), Chinese Functional Communication Profile (CFCP), Communicative Abilities of Daily Living (CADL), and total effective rate, which is the sum of "effective rate" and " markedly effective rate".

11. Additional outcome(s): ① Western Aphasia Battery (WAB);
② Bilingual aphasia test (BAT);
③ Comprehensive Aphasia Test (CAT);
④ Aphasia Rapid Test (ART);
⑤ China Rehabilitation Research Center Aphasia Examination (CRRCAE);
⑥ Aphasia Battery of Chinese (ABC).
If we find other measurements that are suitable and standard for the trials, we will discuss them and decide whether to include them or not.

